TV star and prolific producer Siyabonga Ngwekazi has joined a long list of Mzansi's top celebs who have been taken to court for their income tax affairs, after he was slapped with almost a R200,000 tax bill by the SA Revenue Services (SARS). The taxman obtained judgment against the former Real Goboza presenter at the South Gauteng high court on February 4 after Ngwekazi allegedly failed to settle his outstanding tax dues. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD.